In [61]:
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 5, figsize=(15, 5))

# Names of the columns to plot
columns_to_plot = ['speeding', 'total', 'alcohol','not_distracted','no_previous']

# Loop through the columns and create Q-Q plots
for i, column in enumerate(columns_to_plot):
    ax = axes[i]
    stats.probplot(df[column], dist="norm", plot=ax)
    ax.set_title(f'Q-Q Plot for {column}')

# Adjust layout
plt.tight_layout()

# Show the plot
plt.show()

OBERVATION

We see total and no_previous having the perfect normal distributions when compared with others.

From the graph we can conclude the data is normally distributed and it is not skwed or biased.
